            Hexosyltransferases
SYSNAME     UDP-N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosamine:N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->4)-alpha-D-mannosyl-threonyl-[protein] 3-beta-N-acetyl-D-galactosaminyltransferase
REACTION    UDP-N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosamine + 3-O-[N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->4)-alpha-D-mannosyl]-L-threonyl-[protein] = UDP + 3-O-[N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl-(1->3)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->4)-alpha-D-mannosyl]-L-threonyl-[protein] [RN:R10620]
ALL_REAC    R10620
SUBSTRATE   UDP-N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosamine [CPD:C00203];
            3-O-[N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->4)-alpha-D-mannosyl]-L-threonyl-[protein] [CPD:C20723]
PRODUCT     UDP [CPD:C00015];
            3-O-[N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl-(1->3)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->4)-alpha-D-mannosyl]-L-threonyl-[protein] [CPD:C20734]
COMMENT     The human protein is specific for UDP-N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosamine as donor [1]. The enzyme is involved in the formation of a phosphorylated trisaccharide on a threonine residue of alpha-dystroglycan, an extracellular peripheral glycoprotein that acts as a receptor for extracellular matrix proteins containing laminin-G domains.
